from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
le = LabelEncoder()

df['check_acc'] = le.fit_transform(df['check_acc'])
df['credit_hist'] = le.fit_transform(df['credit_hist'])
df['purpose'] = le.fit_transform(df['purpose'])
df['saving_acc'] = le.fit_transform(df['saving_acc'])
df['present_emp'] = le.fit_transform(df['present_emp'])
df['sex'] = le.fit_transform(df['sex'])
df['other_debtors'] = le.fit_transform(df['other_debtors'])
df['property'] = le.fit_transform(df['property'])
df['other_install_plans'] = le.fit_transform(df['other_install_plans'])
df['housing'] = le.fit_transform(df['housing'])
df['job'] = le.fit_transform(df['job'])
df['telephone'] = le.fit_transform(df['telephone'])
df['foreign'] = le.fit_transform(df['foreign'])
df['risk'] = le.fit_transform(df['risk'])
df['cluster'] = le.fit_transform(df['cluster'])
df

In [10]:
from sklearn.decomposition import PCA
pca = PCA().fit(X)
plt.rcParams["figure.figsize"] = (12,6)

fig, ax = plt.subplots()
xi = np.arange(0, 21, step=1)
y = np.cumsum(pca.explained_variance_ratio_)

plt.ylim(0.0,1.1)
plt.plot(xi, y, marker='o', linestyle='--', color='b')

plt.xlabel('Number of Components')
plt.ylabel('Cumulative variance (%)')
plt.xticks(np.arange(0, 21, step=1))
plt.title('The number of components needed to explain variance')

plt.axhline(y=0.95, color='r', linestyle='-')
plt.text(0.5, 0.85, '95% cut-off threshold', color = 'red', fontsize=12)

ax.grid(axis='x')
plt.show()
In [11]:
pd.DataFrame(data = X, columns = df.columns)
pca = PCA(n_components=3)
principalComponents = pca.fit_transform (X)
principalDf = pd.DataFrame(data = principalComponents, columns=['PC1','PC2','PC3'])
finalDf = pd.concat([principalDf,target['risk']], axis = 1)
fig = plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))
ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
ax.set_xlabel('Principal Component 1', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_ylabel('Principal Component 2', fontsize = 15)
ax.set_title('2-Component PCA', fontsize = 20)

outcomes = [1,0]

colors = ['g','r']

for outcome, color in zip(outcomes,colors):
    indicesToKeep = finalDf['risk'] == outcome
    ax.scatter(finalDf.loc[indicesToKeep, 'PC1']
               , finalDf.loc[indicesToKeep, 'PC2']
               , c = color
               , s = 50)
ax.legend(['Good Risk','Bad Risk'])
plt.show()

import xgboost as xgb
model_xgb=xgb.XGBClassifier(
    objective= 'binary:logistic',
    nthread=4,
    seed=42
)
parameters = {
    'max_depth': range (2, 10, 1),
    'n_estimators': range(60, 220, 40),
    'learning_rate': [0.1, 0.01, 0.05]
}
grid_search_cv = GridSearchCV(
    estimator=model_xgb,
    param_grid=parameters,
    scoring = 'roc_auc',
    n_jobs = 10,
    cv = 10,
    verbose=True
)
grid_search_cv.fit(X_train, y_train)

In [17]:
xgb_clf = grid_search_cv.best_estimator_
xgb_clf.fit(X_train,y_train)
xgb_pred = xgb_clf.predict(X_test)

print('Accuracy:',accuracy_score(xgb_pred,y_test))
print('XGBoost Classification report:')
labels = ['Bad Risk', 'Good Risk']
print(classification_report(xgb_pred,y_test,target_names=labels))

# Let's make sure the data is not overfitting
score_model = cross_val_score(xgb_clf,X_train,y_train, scoring='roc_auc', cv = 10).mean()
print('cross val score:', score_model)

In [19]:
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score
y_pred_prob = xgb_clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob, pos_label = 1)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, lw = 2, label = 'ROC AUC: {:.2f}'.format(roc_auc))
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1],
         linestyle = '--',
         color = (0.6, 0.6, 0.6),
         label = 'random guessing')
plt.plot([0, 0, 1], [0, 1, 1],
         linestyle = ':',
         color = 'black', 
         label = 'perfect performance')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve for XGBoost Classifier')
plt.legend(loc = "lower right")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier

          'n_jobs':[1,2]}
grid_search_cv = GridSearchCV(rfc_clf, params, scoring='roc_auc')
grid_search_cv.fit(X_train, y_train)

from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
# Implement gridsearchcv to see which are our best p

params = {'C': [0.75, 0.85, 0.95, 1], 'kernel': ['linear', 'poly', 'rbf', 'sigmoid'], 
          'degree': [3, 4, 5]}

svc_clf = SVC(random_state=42)
grid_search_cv = GridSearchCV(svc_clf, params, scoring = 'roc_auc')
grid_search_cv.fit(X_train, y_train)

y_pred_prob = svc_clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob, pos_label = 1)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, lw = 2, label = 'ROC AUC: {:.2f}'.format(roc_auc))
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1],
         linestyle = '--',
         color = (0.6, 0.6, 0.6),
         label = 'random guessing')
plt.plot([0, 0, 1], [0, 1, 1],
         linestyle = ':',
         color = 'black', 
         label = 'perfect performance')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve for Support Vector Classifier')
plt.legend(loc = "lower right")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

    "penalty": ['l1', 'l2', 'elasticnet', 'none'],

}

from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc
from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score
y_pred_prob = lr_clf.predict_proba(X_test)[:,1]
fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_prob, pos_label = 1)
roc_auc = auc(fpr, tpr)
plt.plot(fpr, tpr, lw = 2, label = 'ROC AUC: {:.2f}'.format(roc_auc))
plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1],
         linestyle = '--',
         color = (0.6, 0.6, 0.6),
         label = 'random guessing')
plt.plot([0, 0, 1], [0, 1, 1],
         linestyle = ':',
         color = 'black', 
         label = 'perfect performance')
plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
plt.title('ROC Curve for Logistic Regression Classifier')
plt.legend(loc = "lower right")
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
